{"body": "@lest, I think no matter whether it throws an exception or renders `img` tag with empty `src` attribute it'd be better to have same behavior both in default development and production environments. \r\n\r\nRight now with default development environment (without precompiled assets) it generates `<img src=\"/assets\">` or smth like that. The page loads without image and it's easy to miss it. On the other hand in prod environment (with precompiled assets) you get an exception that crashes the whole page while rendering it.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/3937324", "created_at": "2012-02-13T10:31:18Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5020#issuecomment-3937324", "updated_at": "2012-02-13T10:31:18Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 5020, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KL-7/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KL-7/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KL-7/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/KL-7", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KL-7/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/KL-7", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KL-7/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/8d24aa67d897b1505392a31b21308e3c?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fe78841bcb0f29db70700c5aefb8fa342.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KL-7/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KL-7/received_events", "gravatar_id": "8d24aa67d897b1505392a31b21308e3c", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KL-7/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "KL-7", "type": "User", "id": 270365, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/KL-7/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52381dcebd3543c15100e629"}, "id": 3937324, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5020"}
